4: There she is! She's getting away!
7: My, they are tenacious, aren't they?
10:
Don't let her looks deceive you! She's
a wanted criminal! Your reign of
terror en—
12:
*coughing* I-Is this... smoke?! I-I
can't move...
14:
It's h-her! *coughing* The Purple
Haze Rebel!
17:
Oh dear. My sincerest apologies for
causing such a ruckus. Here's a little
something for your troubles.
28:
*wheeze* How about we take... 
a break... by that tree...
32:
Ah, hello there! Would it be all right if
we joined you?
40:
The name's Zelma. You must be
travelers, I presume?
43:
Something like that. We're just on
our way toward the nearest town.
46:
If that's the case, you best be wary
of monsters around these parts.
How about a little something to help
you on your way?
54:
This incense is made of an herb that
has many medicinal properties to
help heal fatigue. I'm actually
something of an herbalist, you see.
59: Wow! That's really kind of you!
63:
You weren't kidding! I really DO feel
better now.
67: Heh-heh... Happy to be of service.
70:
If you liked that one, here's
another—on the house. This one's a
bit different.
75: Really? I mean, we've only just met!
79:
Not at all... These are just a few old
samples I've had lying around.
83:
Well, in that case, I guess we'd be
happy to take them off your hands!
89:
Hehe... I assure you, the pleasure's
all mine.
98:
You know what you've done! And
you really thought you'd get away
with it, didn't you?
100:
And this herb... Just as suspected!
You're co-conspirators of the Purple
Haze Rebel!
103:
Purple Who? Hold on just a second!
Th-that was a gift!
107:
No point trying to talk sense into
them—outta my way!
110:
So you wanna do this the hard way,
huh?
117:
Zelma! What was in that incense?
Did you set us up?!
121:
I can explain later, but how about
we get out of here first?
124:
This isn't exactly the best place for
conversation.
130:
...In other words, you used us as 
decoys so that you could rob 
the Lord's palace for gold?
133:
That was the plan, but I felt bad
leaving you kind strangers high and
dry.
135:
Although from the looks of it, you
probably wouldn't have needed my
help anyways.
139:
That's not the issue here! You stole
and lied... How could you do such
terrible things?!
142:
Your point is? I'm only doing this to
give the people back what was
stolen from them.
147:
So you're robbing the rich... to give to
the poor? How altruistic.
151:
Altru—No! You've got the wrong idea,
weirdo!
153:
I just simply despise those kingdom
stooges, putting their grubby hands
in everyone's business!
161:
While the kingdom may have its
flaws, doing this sort of thing surely
can't end well for you.
165:
Think what you want—I'm gonna lay
low in the meantime.
167:
I'll need somewhere to hide...
Somewhere far away.
183:
Yeah, I can't think of a better place
to harbor someone on the run than
Starview Village.
188:
Starview Village? I've never heard of
such a place, but it sounds interesting 
indeed.
190:
Perhaps it was fate for us to meet
this way. If the invitation still stands,
I'd love to take you up on it.
198:
Hehe... Much obliged. You truly are
an odd group of travelers.
